column1: A birdcage. So this place has one too.
Every Jail we've seen so far has.

But why would Konoe's Jail possess one? Is he
not the mastermind behind all of this?

Konoe's supposed to be the one who created
the Jails.

So he would have to know how they work. It
wouldn't make sense otherwise.

In which case, the only explanation is that he's
trapped himself here with trauma of his own.
Why would he do something like that?
It could be necessary to creating a Jail.

Does that mean Konoe's got some dark past
too?
A guy that confident? I dunno... Doesn't really fit his image, if you ask me.

You said we need a key if we wanna open this
thing, right?

That's correct. And we can get a hint as to its
whereabouts by touching the birdcage.
All right, sure. So I just touch this thing, right?
No, lemme do it. I could use the experience.

Good luck. Make sure you don't let go right
away.
Don't go cryin' on us, Gramps...
Oof, listen to that wolf howl.

I've heard stories of cries that could shake the
heavens. Could this be one of them? It's almost
operatic.

You guys don't even know, man. That shit
seriously hurts!
We do have a dog. Maybe that's what they heard?
It doesn't seem to be Konoe's...
But he said "Akira." Isn't that Konoe's first name?

Whether it was your dog or not, Konoe-san, we
got a tip that you've been physically abusing
your son.

Apparently, Akira-kun has a scar on his arm to
prove it...

Look, he fell over. How many times do I have to
say it?
Are we done here? I'd like to be left alone.

...You little shit! You see all this trouble you're
causing me!?
Keep your goddamn mouth shut and do as I say!
Damn... What the hell was that?

Konoe's past. We were viewing the trauma he
keeps locked away in his heart.
There, there. Good boy. Who's a good wolf?

What am I, your pet!? Yeesh, you guys coulda
warned me about that.
Well, it's not like you asked... Ahaha.
I feel like I've heard that excuse before...

Getting back on track... I heard one of the voices
mention something about abuse.
Was Konoe abused by his father?
It's pretty messed up, but it doesn't justify all the skeevy shit he's been doin'.

Nothing changes the fact that Akira Konoe is an
incredibly dangerous man who changes others'
hearts and robs them of their free will.
Right. We've got to stop him.

So if being abused is the source of his trauma,
then what exactly is his plan here?

We're just gonna have to ask him about it. Up
close and personal!

Yeah, but first we need the key to the
birdcage.

Let's head back to the real world and try to find
the source of that voice.

Was Konoe really treated badly by his own
father?

Zenkichi and Akane were on bad terms, but
nothing like that ever happened between them.

Why did that happen to Konoe? Aren't they
family?
There could be a lot of reasons.
Some hearts are filled with hate.
So some humans are just like that, then...
Joker, do you think family is important?
Can't say I've thought about it.
Yes, I feel like I understand.

I see. So it comes to you so naturally that you
don't even have to think about it?

If I ever get family or friends, I want to support
them as much as I can.
I learned that from the Phantom Thieves.
I wonder how Konoe must've felt back then...
Hey! C'mon, you two, let's get going!
Sorry to keep you waiting. Let's go, Joker!
